<br>
One nice thing is that they removed the Rogues of the White Rose faction hit from some of the quests, so you no longer go KOS at the bank if you do too many of the other quests.  Watch that faction though, if you notice some hits, remember you'll have to take a wide path around the bank area when you run in for your epic.  Only three factions are necessary if you intend to do the epic straight.  Merchants of Halas (don't stress this, you'll default to dubious whatever your faction), Wolves of the North (guards), Shamans of Justice (shamans near Dargon).  Everyone else will be too far off to trouble you, unless as I said you decide to get a little too chummy with the bank wall while you run towards the NPCs.<br>
<br>
I'd go to tricks if you can, it'd be much easier.  Even as an agnostic gnome, I'm dubious in most of Halas, and it's a royal PITA getting faction here.<br>
<br>
